00:58.692 --> 01:01.127
Move it, you're holding everyone up.

01:06.333 --> 01:08.134
And...

01:08.869 --> 01:10.403
...posted.

01:11.538 --> 01:13.206
- You're not helping.
- Helping?

01:13.207 --> 01:14.790
I don't even know what we're doing here

01:14.791 --> 01:16.542
on this kid's obstacle course.

01:16.543 --> 01:18.311
- Training.
- Training?

01:18.312 --> 01:20.213
Oh.

01:20.214 --> 01:21.997
Is there a competition
for getting humiliated

01:21.998 --> 01:23.416
by 12-year-old girls?

01:23.417 --> 01:24.917
'Cause if so, you're kicking butt.

01:24.918 --> 01:26.753
You can make fun all you want.

01:26.754 --> 01:29.555
But I'm gonna make sure
that I'm in primo shape

01:29.556 --> 01:32.258
so whenever I'm needed, I'll be ready.

01:32.259 --> 01:33.760
Ow, ow, ow.

01:33.761 --> 01:35.561
This is about the Vault, isn't it?

01:35.562 --> 01:38.064
You find out that we
work for the same agency,

01:38.065 --> 01:40.066
as Davy Crockett and Sacagawea once did,

01:40.067 --> 01:42.090
and now you're convinced
you need to be James Bond.

01:42.091 --> 01:43.936
Alex, they were heroes,
all right? Legends.

01:43.937 --> 01:45.605
We are not worthy.

01:45.606 --> 01:47.206
Dude, get a grip.

01:47.207 --> 01:49.208
What are you trying to prove?

01:49.209 --> 01:51.577
You just took down a demonic djinn,

01:51.578 --> 01:54.213
and saved a bunch of
lives in the process.

01:54.214 --> 01:56.816
Including mine.

01:56.817 --> 01:58.918
Whoa, whoa, whoa.

01:58.919 --> 02:00.953
Are you saying I'm your hero?

02:02.556 --> 02:04.257
- Hmm?
- You know what?

02:04.258 --> 02:06.401
Next time just let me get
absorbed by the djinn, okay?

02:07.361 --> 02:09.562
I'm a mess.

02:09.562 --> 02:11.097
All right, now.

02:11.098 --> 02:14.167
Will you time me, please?

02:14.168 --> 02:15.868
Okay?

02:15.869 --> 02:17.236
Okay.

02:17.237 --> 02:20.373
I'm good, I'm good.

02:21.942 --> 02:23.710
Don't forget, your interpretations

02:23.711 --> 02:27.046
of Munch's The Scream are due tomorrow.

02:27.047 --> 02:29.182
Or else you might see me screaming.

02:30.284 --> 02:32.051
Hey, Molly.

02:32.052 --> 02:33.675
I noticed your past
couple of assignments

02:33.676 --> 02:35.388
seemed incomplete.

02:35.389 --> 02:36.732
Do you need an extension on them?

02:36.733 --> 02:38.224
I guess.

02:38.225 --> 02:40.226
Our next unit's gonna be a lot of fun.

02:40.227 --> 02:41.850
I know how you like
mixed-media projects.

02:41.851 --> 02:44.163
We're gonna be... Molly.

02:44.164 --> 02:48.034
Molly, Mr. David is speaking to you.

02:48.902 --> 02:51.003
That's okay.

02:56.110 --> 02:57.610
I am so sorry about that.

02:57.611 --> 02:59.412
No worries. I'm used to dealing

02:59.413 --> 03:01.013
with some pretty short attention spans.

03:01.014 --> 03:02.048
Yeah.

03:02.049 --> 03:04.417
But if you don't mind me asking,

03:04.418 --> 03:06.419
is everything okay with Molly at home?

03:06.420 --> 03:08.921
I might be flattering
myself but I thought

03:08.922 --> 03:10.882
- this was her favorite class.
- No, you're right.

03:10.906 --> 03:12.458
- She loves art.
- I'm glad.

03:12.459 --> 03:13.962
That's why I couldn't help but notice

03:13.963 --> 03:15.928
that she just hasn't
been herself lately.

03:15.929 --> 03:18.898
Yeah. Things... have been

03:18.899 --> 03:21.067
a little more complicated
for her lately.

03:21.068 --> 03:23.169
I'd love to discuss this further,

03:23.170 --> 03:25.238
but I've got a faculty meeting.

03:25.239 --> 03:26.472
Can you come by later?

03:26.473 --> 03:28.574
Sure.

03:28.575 --> 03:30.676
Great.

03:40.687 --> 03:43.389
Kind of rough back there with Mr. David.

03:46.160 --> 03:47.493
Guess you're right.

03:47.494 --> 03:48.895
School's overrated.

03:48.896 --> 03:50.329
There are a lot of career options

03:50.330 --> 03:52.732
that don't require an education.

03:52.733 --> 03:55.568
I'm thinking pirates.

03:57.971 --> 03:59.739
Look, I know with everything going on

03:59.740 --> 04:03.109
it seems like school
isn't important, but it is.

04:03.110 --> 04:06.078
It's... really good for us

04:06.079 --> 04:08.648
to keep some normal in our lives.

04:08.649 --> 04:11.017
It's always gonna be like
this from now on, isn't it?

04:11.018 --> 04:15.388
Monsters disguised as Dad.

04:15.389 --> 04:19.158
Logan MacDonald getting
sick from a curse.

04:19.159 --> 04:21.194
Visions of Mr. Crane,

04:21.195 --> 04:23.863
except he's not Mr. Crane.

04:23.864 --> 04:24.564
Molly!

04:24.565 --> 04:27.066
Hello?

04:27.067 --> 04:30.303
He was so scared, Mom, so alone.

04:30.304 --> 04:33.039
We still don't know exactly
what it is that you saw.

04:33.040 --> 04:35.908
It could have been a-a bad dream.

04:37.311 --> 04:38.644
Got an idea.

04:38.645 --> 04:40.146
I've been talking to the others

04:40.147 --> 04:41.290
about showing you something,

04:41.291 --> 04:45.227
but... maybe now's the time.

04:46.186 --> 04:47.753
Showing me something?

04:47.754 --> 04:49.355
What?

04:49.356 --> 04:52.358
Welcome to the Vault.

04:52.359 --> 04:54.594
What is this place?

04:54.595 --> 04:56.729
Uh, the most amazing library ever.

04:56.730 --> 04:59.031
An archive of the incredible.

04:59.032 --> 05:01.634
A repository of the impossible.

05:01.635 --> 05:05.872
A storehouse of secrets great and small.

05:05.873 --> 05:07.206
Whoa.

05:07.207 --> 05:10.810
This... is the untold history

05:10.811 --> 05:12.378
of America, huh?

05:12.379 --> 05:16.782
This is a collection of
weapons from myth and lore.

05:16.783 --> 05:18.117
Huh?

05:18.118 --> 05:19.719
And this...

05:19.720 --> 05:22.788
is classified supernatural information

05:22.789 --> 05:25.358
that's only revealed to
sitting U.S. presidents.

05:25.359 --> 05:27.460
And now... you.

05:28.295 --> 05:29.962
- Hey, kid... Catch.
- Ooh.

05:29.963 --> 05:32.698
What is this?

05:32.699 --> 05:34.282
That is a Native American Thunderstone,

05:34.283 --> 05:36.569
created by the Pawnee Morning Star god.

05:36.570 --> 05:38.313
It's supposed to protect
you from lightning.

05:38.314 --> 05:40.482
I haven't tested it out
yet, if you want to help.

05:43.944 --> 05:47.280
I know you've been through
some dark and scary stuff.

05:47.281 --> 05:50.182
But you also get to
be a part of something

05:50.183 --> 05:53.119
that only a few people in
the whole world know about.

05:53.120 --> 05:57.023
You get to be a part of a secret club.

05:57.024 --> 05:59.425
What do you think?

05:59.426 --> 06:01.594
I think this is really cool.

06:01.595 --> 06:03.596
Good.

06:03.597 --> 06:05.631
Mr. Crane's gonna be
here in a few minutes.

06:05.632 --> 06:07.099
You're not staying?

06:07.100 --> 06:10.202
I have to do some stuff for work, but...

06:10.203 --> 06:12.138
Jake and Alex will show
you anything you want.

06:12.139 --> 06:16.309
Anything that's... not
too dangerous, right?

06:16.310 --> 06:18.177
- Yeah.
- Okay.

06:19.780 --> 06:20.813
Now...

06:20.814 --> 06:23.049
where should we start?

06:38.498 --> 06:40.433
Are you sure about this?

06:40.434 --> 06:43.669
Indian ascetics have used
this method for centuries...

06:43.670 --> 06:46.772
...in pursuit of their visions.

06:46.773 --> 06:50.309
But you seem to have no
trouble accessing your visions.

06:50.310 --> 06:51.978
To a point, Jobe.

06:51.979 --> 06:53.779
I've seen the future to a point.

06:53.780 --> 06:55.014
Now I need

06:55.015 --> 06:56.482
to push past what I've glimpsed.

06:56.483 --> 06:58.984
I need to extend the limits.

07:17.471 --> 07:20.806
I hope you find what you seek, Malcolm.

07:34.154 --> 07:37.523
Hey. Don't move. I'm not finished yet.

07:37.524 --> 07:40.326
I always have so much
trouble with your eyes.

07:40.327 --> 07:42.328
Really?

07:42.329 --> 07:44.063
Would that be because they're so

07:44.064 --> 07:46.499
fantastically full of wisdom?

07:46.500 --> 07:48.501
Well, if I mess this up,

07:48.502 --> 07:50.503
then you'll only have yourself to blame

07:50.504 --> 07:52.004
when your present isn't perfect.

07:52.005 --> 07:54.073
My present?

07:54.074 --> 07:55.441
Of course.

07:55.442 --> 07:56.675
It's a little thank you gift

07:56.676 --> 07:59.111
for everything.

07:59.112 --> 08:00.780
Can we fly the glider tomorrow?

08:01.882 --> 08:04.050
A girl after my own heart.

08:04.051 --> 08:06.318
I can't deny you anything, now, can I?

08:22.702 --> 08:26.605
So... was the future
different this time?

08:26.606 --> 08:30.176
It's still the future I'm
destined to bring about.

08:32.746 --> 08:35.681
But it's far superior this time.

08:35.682 --> 08:37.183
How so?

08:39.052 --> 08:42.188
I'm not alone.

08:45.092 --> 08:46.592
Master Wells and Miss Alex

08:46.593 --> 08:48.394
will return shortly with our repast.

08:48.395 --> 08:50.262
Cool. Pizza?

08:50.263 --> 08:52.398
Something a little more delectable

08:52.399 --> 08:54.633
than Neapolitan flatbread.

08:54.634 --> 08:56.569
Well, look at that.

08:58.405 --> 09:01.941
You know this was actually
worn by Davy Crockett.

09:01.942 --> 09:03.442
True.

09:03.443 --> 09:05.578
Now, legend would have you believe

09:05.579 --> 09:08.781
that this was fashioned
from common raccoon.

09:08.782 --> 09:10.916
But between you and me,

09:10.917 --> 09:13.252
this is actually Wendigo pelt.

09:13.253 --> 09:14.987
Wendi what?

09:14.988 --> 09:16.922
Wendigo.

09:16.923 --> 09:18.224
It's a shape-shifting beast

09:18.225 --> 09:20.726
of Shawnee and Algonquian legend.

09:24.164 --> 09:25.498
Monsters.

09:25.499 --> 09:26.799
Monsters.

09:26.800 --> 09:28.534
Where do they come from?

09:30.403 --> 09:32.004
Purgatory.

09:32.005 --> 09:34.507
Hell dimensions.

09:34.508 --> 09:36.642
Hidden pockets of existence

09:36.643 --> 09:39.078
of which we are only dimly aware.

09:39.079 --> 09:43.015
And they just roam
around like wild animals?

09:43.016 --> 09:45.951
Some do.

09:45.952 --> 09:48.687
Mostly they appear when summoned.

09:48.688 --> 09:51.524
When a person wishes to perpetrate evil.

09:51.525 --> 09:54.827
So bad people means bad monsters.

09:54.828 --> 09:59.031
Now that is very aptly put.

09:59.032 --> 10:01.233
I know a good monster.

10:01.234 --> 10:02.735
A good monster?

10:02.736 --> 10:04.069
Finally.

10:04.070 --> 10:05.738
Yeah.

10:05.739 --> 10:07.339
I made him up when I was little.

10:07.340 --> 10:09.243
He's one of the first
things I remember drawing.

10:09.244 --> 10:12.478
His body was my favorite blanket.

10:12.479 --> 10:15.881
Whenever I was scared or lonely,

10:15.882 --> 10:18.050
he'd be there for me.

10:18.051 --> 10:20.019
I call him Mr. Stitch.

10:20.020 --> 10:21.353
Oh.

10:23.690 --> 10:27.693
It is a pleasure to make
your acquaintance, Mr. Stitch.

10:27.694 --> 10:30.162
He used to sing me this song.

11:20.652 --> 11:27.552
